svdint4 includes an Apache-2.0 derived minimal binding around the Nunchaku
W4A4/SVDQuant CUDA kernel path.

Only the INT4 GEMM, activation quantization, and fused SVD LoRA path are
exposed here. Model wrappers, attention/RoPE/RMSNorm fusion, W8A8, AWQ,
NVFP4, cache logic, and pipeline integrations are intentionally omitted.

The flattened CUDA kernel subset under csrc/ is derived from Nunchaku:

  https://github.com/nunchaku-ai/nunchaku

Nunchaku is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. A copy of the
original license text is kept in LICENSES/nunchaku-LICENCE.txt.

The derived subset has been reduced and flattened to the files required for
INT4 GEMM, activation quantization, and fused SVD LoRA dispatch. The package
build no longer depends on a sibling nunchaku checkout.
